BRIEFING:
A RAPIDLY-MOVING SURFACE HIGH WILL PASS N OF THE ISLANDS TODAY, SUPPORTING MODERATE E TRADE WINDS. AS THE HIGH MOVES AWAY TO THE NE TONIGHT, THE ASSOCIATED RIDGE WILL MOVE TO A POSITION JUST N OF KAUAI. THIS WILL LEAD TO LIGHTER SE WINDS OVER KAUAI AND OAHU, AND LIGHT TO MODERATE ESE WINDS OVER MAUI AND HAWAII COUNTIES. LAND AND SEA BREEZES WILL BE LIKELY OVER SHELTERED LEEWARD AREAS, LEADING TO SOME CLOUDS OVER LEEWARD AND INTERIOR AREAS. OUTSIDE OF ISOL MVFR CIG, VFR CONDITIONS WILL PREVAIL AND NO AIRMETS ARE EXPECTED.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
